* Markdown
  :PROPERTIES:
  :CUSTOM_ID: markdown
  :END:

#+BEGIN_QUOTE
  Markdown is a text-to-HTML conversion tool for web writers.\\
  Markdown allows you to write using an easy-to-read, easy-to-write
  plain text format, then convert it to structurally valid XHTML (or
  HTML).
#+END_QUOTE

-  [[https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/][markdown]]

** Markdown syntax
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: markdown-syntax
   :END:

-  [[https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax][markdown syntax]]

** The Markdown file extension
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: the-markdown-file-extension
   :END:

John Gruber didn't designated a file extension when he invented Markdown

#+BEGIN_QUOTE
  John Gruber\\
  The only file extension I would endorse is “.markdown” (I personally
  use “.text” for my own files, and have BBEdit set to use Markdown
  syntax coloring for that extension, which is why I never saw a need to
  endorse an official extension.)
#+END_QUOTE

** Different Markdown file extension
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: different-markdown-file-extension
   :END:

- markdown
- mdown
- mkdn
- md
- mkd
- mdwn
- mdtxt
- mdtext
- text

*** Markdown extensions used by different editors
    :PROPERTIES:
    :CUSTOM_ID: markdown-extensions-used-by-different-editors
    :END:

-  GitHub: markdown, mdown, mkdn, mkd, md (source)
-  Elements Markdown Editor: markdown, mdown, mdwn, md
-  Vim markdown: markdown, mdown, mkdn, mdwn, mkd, md
-  Bitbucket: markdown, mdown, mkdn, mkd, md, text (source)
   
